  <h1>
   phy_speed_x
  </h1>
  This variable can be used to get or change the x component of the instance's linear speed vector and is defined in pixels per step (for pixels per second, see
  <a href="phy_linear_velocity_x.htm">
   <span>
    phy_linear_velocity_x
   </span>
  </a>
  ). Altering this for a static instance (ie: an instance with 0 density) will turn it into a kinematic instance.
  <h4>
   Syntax:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">phy_speed_x;
</code></pre>
  <h4>
   Returns:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml"><a href="../../../../../GameMaker_Language/GML_Overview/Data_Types.htm">
 Real
</a>
(single precision floating point value, or undefined if the instance is not physics enabled)
</code></pre>
  <h4>
   Example:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">if phy_speed_x != 0
{
    phy_speed_x = 0;
}
</code></pre>
  The above code will check the x component of the linear speed vector and if it is anything other than 0 it will set it to 0.
 </body>
</html>